reviewText: only two of the three movies are horror the third was more of a shoot em' up but over all I liked all three movie great if you are in to Japanese cinma the weak link in this set in my opion was samurai chicks. the other two were pretty good
Just wild japanese horror genre fare!
Tokyo Shock Always Delivers. There Movies Are so Outrageous They Are Unique. Its Unbelievable Entertainment But Thats Why I Dig It So. Lucky To Have found This On Amazon.  Michael Jacobsen
A fun little collection. Features an older 70's style horror film, a great campy modern horror, and an action film. A good example of Tokyo shocks products.

I love this Horror DVDs.  Japanese Hell... was a bit Gross, but interesting as you didn't know what comes next.  The Opening of the Gates to Hell was Amusing because it reminded me of a Big Ol VAG..... as funny as some of the Lyrics from Blowfly's Oldies but Goodies.
